<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,470,525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,471,495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Radoszkowski, 1885" authorityName="Radoszkowski" authorityYear="1885" box="[300,709,470,495]" class="Reptilia" family="Agamidae" genus="Agama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="komarovii">
<emphasis box="[300,484,471,495]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Agama komarovii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Radoszkowski, O." box="[493,709,470,495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="3 - 49" refId="ref19784" refString="Radoszkowski, O. (1885) Revision des armures copulatrices des males de la famille de Mutillides. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Rossicae, 19 (1 - 2), 3 - 49, 9 pls." type="journal article" year="1885">Radoszkowski, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<specimenCount box="[723,744,471,494]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, by subsequent designation of Ashmead 1903: 305 (misspelled as 
<emphasis box="[199,299,502,525]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Kamarovi</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,571,670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">
Twenty-five species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1896" box="[418,608,571,597]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudophotopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[418,608,571,597]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Pseudophotopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from arid areas of the Palaearctic; a few penetrate to the Afrotropical and Oriental regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Pagliano, G. &amp; Brothers, D. J. &amp; Cambra, R. &amp; Lelej, A. S. &amp; Lo Cascio, P. &amp; Matteini Palmerini, M. &amp; Scaramozzino, P. L. &amp; Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M." box="[516,751,607,634]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64" pagination="5 - 425" refId="ref19407" refString="Pagliano, G., Brothers, D. J., Cambra, R., Lelej, A. S., Lo Cascio, P., Matteini Palmerini, M., Scaramozzino, P. L., Williams, K. A. &amp; Romano, M. (2020 [&quot; 2018 &quot;]) Checklist of names in Mutillidae (Hymenoptera), with illustrations of selected species. Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali di Torino, 36 (1 - 2), 5 - 425." type="journal article" year="2020">
Pagliano 
<emphasis box="[624,681,607,633]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). They are mainly nocturnal. Three species of this genus are distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[305,432,643,669]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
. One of them is recorded from this country for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
